## Summary

### File changed
**`proofs/lean/extraction/SquareObligations.lean`**

### What was added

**`square_ok`** — proves the postcondition (no overflow → returns `x * x`):
```lean
theorem square_ok (x : u8) (h : ¬ UInt8.mulOverflow x x) :
    square.square x = RustM.ok (x * x) := by
  simp only [UInt8.mulOverflow] at h          -- rewrite h: ¬ BitVec.umulOverflow …
  simp only [square.square,
             rust_primitives.ops.arith.Mul.mul,
             if_neg h]                         -- unfold def, pick else-branch
  rfl                                          -- pure (x*x) = RustM.ok (x*x) by reducibility
```

**`square_overflow`** — proves the failure condition (overflow → `integerOverflow`):
```lean
theorem square_overflow (x : u8) (h : UInt8.mulOverflow x x) :
    square.square x = RustM.fail Error.integerOverflow := by
  simp only [UInt8.mulOverflow] at h          -- rewrite h: BitVec.umulOverflow … = true
  simp only [square.square,
             rust_primitives.ops.arith.Mul.mul,
             if_pos h]                         -- unfold def, pick then-branch (closed by rfl internally)
```

### Key sub-goals and how they were resolved

| Sub-goal | Resolution |
|---|---|
| Connecting `UInt8.mulOverflow` to `BitVec.umulOverflow` | `simp only [UInt8.mulOverflow] at h` — `mulOverflow` is definitionally `BitVec.umulOverflow a.toBitVec b.toBitVec`, so simp rewrites `h` to match the `if` condition inside `Mul.mul` |
| Unfolding `square.square` and `*?` | `simp only [square.square, rust_primitives.ops.arith.Mul.mul]` — `@[spec]` does not block `simp`; the macro-generated `Mul UInt8` instance expands the `if`-expression |
| `pure (x * x) = RustM.ok (x * x)` | `rfl` — both sides reduce to `some (Except.ok (x * x))` under reducible transparency (`RustM.ok` is `@[reducible]`) |
| `RustM.fail Error.integerOverflow = RustM.fail Error.integerOverflow` | Closed automatically by `simp only [if_pos h]` (syntactically equal after elaboration) |

### Obligations admitted
None — both theorems are fully proved.

